modules.description: Handles biometric authentication requests using device-specific sensors, including checking availability and initiating a verification prompt. Works with boolean flags indicating sensor presence and error messages from authentication attempts. Used to secure user login flows and confirm sensitive actions like financial transactions.

Authenticates a user with biometric data, invoking success or failure callbacks based on the result, and checks if biometric authentication is supported on the device, returning a status message. It operates with callback functions and string error messages. Used to secure user login flows and verify device compatibility with biometric features.
